6.3 Laboratories: Maintenance and overall ambiance (10)
Total Marks 10.00
Open Seperately Institute Marks
Please Enter Marks Marks cannot be greater than max Marks

Maintenance:

  1. All the equip ments are serviced regularly before the commencement of semester.
  2. Equipment is regularly checked & maintained by the technicians in the respective labs.
  3. Laboratories cleaning and maintenance is done by Housekeeping committee.
  4. Electrical problems and repairs are done by electrical maintenance committee.
  5. Computer and Networking problems rectified by Computer and Networking maintenance committee.
  6. Servicing of equipment is done by External Technician if required.
  7. The components / equip ments are tested thoroughly by the technicians before and after conducting experiments by the students.
  8. All the systems are installed with Licensed and open source Softwares.

Overall ambiance of laboratories:

  1. Department has adequate well equipped laboratories to meet the Curriculum requirements and beyond too.
  2. All laboratories are well ventilated.
  3. All the software labs are provided with air conditioners.
  4. Each hardware lab is equipped with computer along with suitable software
  5. List of Experiments as per the Curriculum is displayed.
  6. DOs and Donts are displayed.
  7. Laboratory manuals are prepared and are available in soft and hard copy.
  8. Display Charts are displayed.

EDCLAB

EDC/ECALABS:

This laboratory enables the students of II year ECE to gain practical experience in connecting circuits with discrete components and testing the circuits.

Major facilities/equipment:

  • Dual Trace Cathode Ray Oscilloscopes
  • Function Generators
  • Regulated Power Supplies
  • Multi-meters
  • Bread Board
  • Trainer Modules

IC& PDC LAB

ADICA/AICA LAB:

This laboratory enables the students of III year ECE to gain practical experience in connecting circuits with discrete components and testing the circuits.

Major facilities/equipment:

  • Dual Trace Cathode Ray Oscilloscopes
  • 10MHzFunctionGenerators
  • Regulated DC Power Supplies
  • General purpose IC Trainer
  • OP-AMP Trainer kit
  • Bread Board Trainer Modules
  • Servo Stabilizer

COMMUNICATION LAB

AC/DC/STLD/ADC LAB:

This enables students of II and III-year ECE to understand analog and Digital communication circuits using training kits.

Major facilities/equipment:

  • Dual Trace Cathode Ray Oscilloscopes
  • Digital Storage Oscilloscope
  • 10MHzFunctionGenerators
  • Regulated DC Power Supplies

ECADLAB

DSP/ AC /OOPS Thru JAVA/DS Through JAVA/IP/CNS LAB:

This laboratory is equipped with Computers to educate the II&III-year ECE students in simulation of signal processing systems functionality using MATLAB.

Major facilities/equipment:

  • DesktopDualcore3.22GBRAM, 320 GB HDD, Key boards, Mouses,18.5 TFT Monitors(Acer)
  • MATLAB
  • DSPStarterkitsDSPTMS320C6713, 512 k flash and 16 MBSDRAM code composer studio V3.1 IDE including the fast simulator and access to Analysis kit(Texas)

VLSILAB

DICD/VLSI/IOT/ARM Program/PYTHON/DESIGNER TOOLSLAB:

This laboratory enables the students of II, III & IV-year students to gain practical experience in designing and developing IOT systems using Arduino and Raspberry pi boards and other components

Major facilities/equipment:

  • PCs, Arduino open-source software development tool,
  • ARM7boards,
  • Arduino UNO boards,
  • Raspberry pi boards
  • Various other interfacing kits and necessary software packages

PROCESSOR &

MICRO CONTROLLER

LAB

MP&MC LAB:

  • This label so provides various equipment for III& IV year students to perform experiments in the area of Micro Processors & Micro Controllers, microwave and optical Communications.

Major facilities/equipment:

  • 8086 Micro Processors
  • 8051 Micro Controllers
  • Dual Trace Cathode Ray Oscilloscopes
  • Microwave Test benches
  • Klystron/Gunn Power Supplies

  • VSWR Meters
  • Optical Communications Kits
  • Servo Stabilizer

PROJECT LAB

PROJECT LAB

This laboratory is well equipped Computers and oscilloscope with other tools and equipment for major R&D projects.

Usage:

Used by Faculty and students for the development of mini and major projects and R&D Projects.

Major facilities/equipment:

  • IC Tester
  • Cathode ray oscilloscope
  • Regulated power supply
  • Function Generator
  • Digital storage oscilloscope



6.4 Project laboratories (5)
Total Marks 5.00
Open Seperately Institute Marks
Mention facilities & Utilization
Please Enter Marks Marks cannot be greater than max Marks

Students are required to do mini project and major projects during IV year I and II semesters respectively. They are allowed to do projects outside the campus to get industrial exposure and also are allowed to do In-house projects under the guidance of department faculty. The Project Laboratory offers the students, opportunity to gain valuable hands-on experience with the state- of-the-art environment where students become proficient in both the technical and creative skills needed in the field of Electronics and Communication Engineering. The Project Laboratory has a key role in promoting practical learning experience and is a place where they develop creative proposals and execute their final year projects.

  1. The following are the facilities which can be used for Project Laboratory:
